description:
hi!
When we want to use order by, with LIMIT and OFFSET, with datasets over 10000 rows, e.g., LIMIT 100 OFFSET 14000 we get error:

Virtuoso 22023 Error SR353: Sorted TOP clause specifies more then 14100 rows to sort. Only 10000 are allowed. Either decrease the offset and/or row count or use a scrollable cursor

In order to avoid this error we are using subqueries as suggested in Working with SPARQL endpoint constraints via LIMIT & OFFSET
However, there is a problem when using MAX (in group) function. We need MAX because there are some sosa:ObservationCollection with more than one sosa:resultTime/sosa:phenomenonTime and we just need to take one
For example, see queries below (you can test in https://www.foodie-cloud.org/sparql)

query 1 returns the first 100 rows correctly, but the ORDER BY is ignored. Rows are returned in random? order
the query 2 returns rows in correct order, but the LIMIT and OFFSET are ignored

Is there a way to make both work properly, where all, ORDER BY, plus LIMIT and OFFSET work properly?
Query1
PREFIX sosa:  <http://www.w3.org/ns/sosa/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?id MAX(?phenomenonTime) as ?p MAX(?resultTime) as ?r

FROM <http://w3id.org/iliad/dataaset/jf-pilot-sample>

WHERE {
    SELECT DISTINCT ?id ?phenomenonTime ?resultTime
    WHERE {
        ?col    a                           sosa:ObservationCollection;
                sosa:resultTime             ?resultTime;
                sosa:phenomenonTime         ?phenomenonTime;
                sosa:hasMember              ?s.
        ?s      rdf:type/rdfs:subClassOf*   sosa:Observation;
                sosa:hasResult              ?result.

        BIND(REPLACE(STRAFTER(STR(?s), "observation/"), "/", "-") AS ?id)

    }
    ORDER BY ?id
}
GROUP BY ?id
LIMIT 100 OFFSET 0
Query2
PREFIX sosa:  <http://www.w3.org/ns/sosa/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?id ?p ?r

FROM <http://w3id.org/iliad/dataaset/jf-pilot-sample>

WHERE {
    SELECT DISTINCT ?id MAX(?phenomenonTime) as ?p MAX(?resultTime) as ?r
    FROM <http://w3id.org/iliad/dataaset/jf-pilot-sample>
    WHERE {
        ?col    a                           sosa:ObservationCollection;
                sosa:resultTime             ?resultTime;
                sosa:phenomenonTime         ?phenomenonTime;
                sosa:hasMember              ?s.
        ?s      rdf:type/rdfs:subClassOf*   sosa:Observation;
                sosa:hasResult              ?result.

        BIND(REPLACE(STRAFTER(STR(?s), "observation/"), "/", "-") AS ?id)

    }
    GROUP BY ?id
    ORDER BY ?id
}
LIMIT 100 OFFSET 0
